      </a>
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_8fe201d8-eee2-4930-b00e-09fd5add5499" class="text-block-content">
    <p>Click the name of the discussion.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="show-rubric" data-step-uuid="7b77ba46-3b05-4b46-a414-b75676cd858f">
    <h2 id="show-rubric" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Show Rubric</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/004/681/795/original/4ff4c50a-b432-4a7d-a7a6-f7d0b21e1fc0.png" srcset="" alt="Show Rubric" height="424" width="852">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_d9ea2dc1-4123-43b6-be79-da4a8778d6dd" class="text-block-content">
    <p>Click the <strong>Options</strong> icon [1] and select the <strong>Show Rubric</strong> link [2].</p>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> If a rubric has not been added to a discussion, the Options menu includes a <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-add-a-rubric-to-a-graded-discussion/ta-p/1062" target="_blank">Add Rubric link</a>.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="view-rubric" data-step-uuid="907a2f66-fc97-43d8-85c2-e8bc3a52fab6">
    <h2 id="view-rubric" class="step-title screensteps-heading">View Rubric</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/004/681/798/original/3cb56060-e32b-4f24-bc6d-427188b903f0.png" srcset="" alt="View Rubric" height="570" width="604">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_8bed21a1-b049-4d93-a0bb-5255cebb08b5" class="text-block-content">
    <p>View the rubric.</p>
<p>To edit the rubric, click the <strong>Edit</strong> icon [1]. To find an existing rubric to replace the current rubric, click the <strong>Find</strong> icon [2]. To remove the rubric from the discussion, click the <strong>Delete</strong> icon [3].</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>
					
				
			
			
			
				
			
			
			
			
			
			
